{
  "_comment": "Copy this file to secrets.local.json (same folder) and fill in your rcon_password per profile. secrets.local.json is GITIGNORED and never committed. Keys are the profile NAMES shown in the panel's server dropdown ('VPS' = the remote box, 'Local' = this machine's own server over loopback); values are that server's rcon_password (<=23 chars — Plutonium silently ignores longer). Leave a value blank ('') for a server with no rcon_password. The panel reads/writes this file over its loopback-only API, so you can also just type the password into the panel once and it saves here automatically.",
  "profiles": {
    "VPS": "",
    "Local": ""
  }
}
